<LegalLayout
  title="Pairloom Privacy Policy — Victor Odukoya"
  description="Privacy Policy for Pairloom - Learn Anything with Pairs."
  lastUpdated="January 16, 2026"
>
  <p class="lead">
    This Privacy Policy specifically covers the Pairloom app. Please also review our
    <a href="/privacy">General Privacy Policy</a> for information that applies to all our
    apps and services.
  </p>

  <h2>1. About Pairloom</h2>
  <p>
    Pairloom is a learning app that helps you master any topic through pair-matching games.
    You can create custom catalogs of word pairs, use AI to generate content, and track your
    learning progress.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Data We Collect in Pairloom</h2>

  <h3>2.1 User Content</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Catalogs:</strong> Custom catalogs you create, including names, descriptions, and pairs</li>
    <li><strong>Progress Data:</strong> XP, levels, streaks, achievements, and mastery tracking</li>
    <li><strong>Settings:</strong> App preferences, theme choices, and notification settings</li>
    <li><strong>Groups:</strong> Organizational groups for your catalogs</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.2 Gameplay Data</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Session statistics (pairs solved, time, accuracy)</li>
    <li>Game mode preferences</li>
    <li>Difficulty adaptation metrics</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.3 AI Generation Data</h3>
  <p>When you use AI to generate catalogs:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your prompt/topic is sent to Google Gemini AI</li>
    <li>We do not store your prompts on our servers</li>
    <li>Generated content is stored locally and optionally in cloud sync</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Data Storage</h2>

  <h3>3.1 Local Storage (Default)</h3>
  <p>
    By default, all your data is stored locally on your device using SQLite. This includes
    catalogs, progress, settings, and all gameplay data. This data never leaves your device
    unless you enable cloud sync.
  </p>

  <h3>3.2 Cloud Sync (Pro Feature)</h3>
  <p>If you enable cloud sync:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your data is encrypted and uploaded to Supabase (AWS infrastructure)</li>
    <li>Data is associated with your account (Google Sign-In)</li>
    <li>You can restore your data on any device</li>
    <li>Data is retained for 30 days after subscription cancellation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Advertisements</h2>
  <p>
    Pairloom displays advertisements to free users via Google AdMob. These ads may use
    device identifiers and cookies to serve personalized content.
  </p>
  <p>You can:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Opt out of personalized ads in the app settings</li>
    <li>Upgrade to Pro to remove all advertisements</li>
    <li>Manage ad preferences through your device settings</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We comply with GDPR and CCPA requirements for advertising consent.
  </p>

  <h2>5. In-App Purchases</h2>
  <p>
    Pairloom Pro subscriptions are processed through the App Store (iOS) or Google Play
    (Android). We use RevenueCat to manage subscriptions.
  </p>
  <p>We receive:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Subscription status (active, expired, trial)</li>
    <li>Product purchased and pricing</li>
    <li>Anonymous subscriber identifiers</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do NOT receive your payment details (credit card, etc.). These are handled securely
    by Apple or Google.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Notifications</h2>
  <p>Pairloom may send local notifications for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Daily streak reminders (if enabled)</li>
    <li>Learning goal reminders (if configured)</li>
    <li>Achievement celebrations</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You can manage notification settings within the app or through your device settings.
    Notifications are generated locally and do not require internet.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Offline Functionality</h2>
  <p>
    Pairloom is designed to work fully offline. All core features including gameplay,
    progress tracking, and catalog management work without an internet connection.
  </p>
  <p>Features requiring internet:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>AI-powered catalog generation</li>
    <li>Cloud backup and sync</li>
    <li>Account sign-in/sign-out</li>
    <li>Subscription verification</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. Data Export and Deletion</h2>

  <h3>8.1 Export Your Data</h3>
  <p>
    You can export all your Pairloom data (catalogs, progress, settings) from the app
    settings. Data is exported in JSON format.
  </p>

  <h3>8.2 Delete Your Data</h3>
  <p>To delete your Pairloom data:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Local data:</strong> Uninstall the app or use "Clear Data" in settings</li>
    <li><strong>Cloud data:</strong> Delete your account from the app settings</li>
    <li><strong>Full deletion:</strong> Contact us at the email below</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>9. Age Restrictions</h2>
  <p>
    Pairloom is rated 4+ (Everyone) on app stores but is designed for users 13 and older.
    We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
  </p>

